revision.text:
'''Bwana Tamu''' was  Sultan of [[Pate Island#Pate Town|Pate]], [[Kenya]], from 1713. 
He decided to wage a war on [[Lamu]] in order to get the guns that the [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] had buried on [[Lamu Island]], on Hedabu Hill. However, his boats were overloaded with fire-arms and they sank on the way to Lamu.<ref>Martin, 1973, p. 7</ref>

