{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2014}} {{Infobox person | name = Julie Klausner | image = Julie Klausner April 2013.jpg | caption = Julie Klausner in April 2013 | birth_date = {{birth date and age| mf=yes|1978|7|3}} | birth_place = [[New York City]], U.S. | alma_mater = [[New York University]] | years_active = 1998–present | occupation = {{flatlist| *Writer *comedian *author}} }}
'''Julie Klausner''' (born July 3, 1978) is an American author, comedian, podcaster, and writer. She is best known for creating, writing and starring in the [[Hulu]] sitcom ''[[Difficult People]]'' (2015-2017) alongside [[Billy Eichner]].
==Early life== Klausner was born in [[New York City]] and grew up in [[Scarsdale, New York]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/10/arts/television/julie-klausner-difficult-people-season-two.html|title=Julie Klausner’s Comic Success With ‘Difficult People’|date=10 July 2016|work=The New York Times|accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref> is a graduate of [[New York University]] and studied at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade]] and the [[School of Visual Arts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/08/05/meet-one-difficult-people-julie-klausner|title=Meet one of the 'Difficult People': Julie Klausner|publisher=[[ew.com]]|accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politico.com/states/new-york/albany/story/2012/12/mrs-shandy-the-life-and-opinions-of-julie-klausner-comedian-000000|title='Mrs. Shandy': The life and opinions of Julie Klausner, comedian|publisher=[[Politico]]|accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/01/arts/julie-klausners-podcast-how-was-your-week.html| title=A Podcast That Has Old-School Smarts| work=[[The New York Times]]| date=31 December 2012| accessdate=3 July 2015| first=Jason| last=Zinoman}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sva.edu/feed-item/sva-alumnus-julie-klausner-profiled-in-the-new-york-times|title=School of Visual Arts - SVA - New York City > Trending Now > SVA Alumnus Julie Klausner Profiled in 'The New York Times'|publisher=sva.edu|accessdate=13 July 2016}}</ref>
==Career== Klausner was the writer and co-star of the [[Hulu]] sitcom ''[[Difficult People]]'', with comedian [[Billy Eichner]]. Produced by [[Amy Poehler]], the series debuted on August 5, 2015,<ref>{{cite web| url=http://entertainthis.usatoday.com/2015/06/30/watch-a-trailer-for-amy-poehlers-new-show-difficult-people/| work=[[USA Today]]| title=Watch a trailer for Amy Poehler's new show, 'Difficult People'| date=6 April 2011| accessdate=3 July 2015| first=Andrea | last=Mandell}}</ref> and [[Difficult People#Season 2 .282016.29|Season 2]] premiered on July 12, 2016. Season 3 of ''Difficult People'' premiered on August 8, 2017. On November 14, 2017, it was announced that Hulu had canceled ''Difficult People.'' All 28 episodes will remain available on the streaming service.
Klausner is head writer and co-executive producer of ''[[Billy on the Street]]'', also starring Eichner. Klausner has written for television programs like ''[[Mulaney]]'', ''[[Best Week Ever]]'', ''[[The Big Gay Sketch Show]]'', ''[[The Jack and Triumph Show]]'', as well as pop culture websites like ''[[The Awl]]'' and ''[[New York (magazine)#Digital expansion and blogs|Vulture]]''.<ref>{{cite web| title=Julie Klausner at The Awl| url=http://www.theawl.com/tag/julie-klausner | first=Julie| last=Klausner| accessdate=4 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nymag.com/author/Julie%20Klausner/|title=List of Julie Klausner articles|last=|first=|date=22 August 2016|website=|publisher=|access-date=22 August 2016}}</ref> In 2012, ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine featured her podcast ''[[How Was Your Week with Julie Klausner|How Was Your Week?]]'' in their list of "10 Best Comedy Podcasts of the Moment".<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/the-10-best-comedy-podcasts-of-the-moment-20110406/| title=The 10 Best Comedy Podcasts of the Moment| work=[[Rolling Stone]]| date=6 April 2011| accessdate=12 October 2012| first=Joe| last=Berkowitz}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/01/arts/julie-klausners-podcast-how-was-your-week.html| title=A Podcast That Has Old-School Smarts| work=[[The New York Times]]| date=31 December 2012| accessdate=3 July 2015| first=Jason| last=Zinoman}}</ref> In October 2011, ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' reported that [[NBC]] had picked up a [[television pilot|pilot]] based on Sue Margolis's novel, ''Apocalipstick'', about a woman's father that dates her high-school nemesis; Klausner was set to write and executive produce the series.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nbc-gail-berman-lloyd-braun-253279| work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]| title=NBC Buys 'Apocalipstick' Comedy, 'Masters and Apprentice' Drama from BermanBraun (Exclusive)| first=Lacey| last=Rose| first2=Lesley| last2=Goldberg| date=25 October 2011| accessdate=12 October 2011}}</ref> In March 2018, it was announced that Klausner would co-star in [[NBC]]'s comedy pilot ''So Close''.<ref>https://deadline.com/2018/03/so-close-julie-klausner-cast-nbc-comedy-pilot-1202346536/</ref>
===Books=== Klausner's first book, ''[[I Don't Care About Your Band]]'', was released in February 2010 by [[Penguin Group|Gotham]]/[[Penguin Books]].<ref>{{cite web | title=I Don't Care About Your Band| url=https://www.amazon.com/Dont-Care-About-Your-Band/dp/159240561| work=[[Penguin Group|Gotham]]| isbn=978-1592405619 | date=2 February 2010| access-date=3 July 2015| first=Julie| last=Klausner}}</ref> In July 2010, it was announced that [[Will Ferrell]] and [[Adam McKay]]'s production company, [[Gary Sanchez Productions]], optioned the book for [[HBO]]. [[Lizzy Caplan]] was attached to star and co-produce.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/07/hbo-develops-band-comedy-with-will-ferrell-adam-mckay-and-lizzy-caplan/|title=HBO Develops 'Band' Comedy With Will Ferrell, Adam McKay and Lizzy Caplan| website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]| date=29 July 2010| accessdate=12 October 2012| first=Nellie| last=Andreeva}}</ref> In 2013, Klausner published her first [[young adult fiction|young adult novel]] entitled ''Art Girls Are Easy''.<ref>{{cite web| title=Art Girls Are Easy| url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/0316243620| work=[[Amazon.com|Amazon]] | isbn=978-0316243629| date=7 May 2013| access-date=3 July 2015| first=Julie| last=Klausner}}</ref>
