{{Eastern Slavic name|Saidbegovich|Asildarov}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Shamil Asildarov | fullname = Shamil Saidbegovich Asildarov | image = ShAsildarov.JPG | image_size = 200px | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1983|5|18|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Makhachkala]], [[Dagestan]], [[Russia]] | height = {{height|meters=1.86}} | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2000–2004 | clubs1 = [[FC Dynamo Makhachkala|Dynamo Makhachkala]] | caps1 = 165 | goals1 = 93 | years2 = 2005 | clubs2 = [[FC Khimki|Khimki]] | caps2 = 9 | goals2 = 4 | years3 = 2006 | clubs3 = [[FC Kuban Krasnodar|Kuban Krasnodar]] | caps3 = 20 | goals3 = 18 | years4 = 2006 | clubs4 = [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]] | caps4 = 4 | goals4 = 1 | years5 = 2007 | clubs5 = [[FC Kuban Krasnodar|Kuban Krasnodar]] | caps5 = 13 | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2007 | clubs6 = [[FC Terek Grozny|Terek Grozny]] | caps6 = 12 | goals6 = 4 | years7 = 2008 | clubs7 = [[FC Anzhi Makhachkala|Anzhi Makhachkala]] | caps7 = 21 | goals7 = 6 | years8 = 2008 | clubs8 = [[FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok|Luch-Energiya]] | caps8 = 9 | goals8 = 1 | years9 = 2009 | clubs9 = [[PFC Spartak Nalchik|Spartak Nalchik]] | caps9 = 14 | goals9 = 8 | years10 = 2010–2012 | clubs10 = [[FC Terek Grozny|Terek Grozny]] | caps10 = 65 | goals10 = 17 | years11 = 2012–2013 | clubs11 = [[FC Volga Nizhny Novgorod|Volga Nizhny Novgorod]] | caps11 = 13 | goals11 = 3 | years13 = 2014 | clubs13 = [[FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok|Luch-Energiya]] | caps13 = 11 | goals13 = 5 | years14 = 2014–2015 | clubs14 = [[FC Anzhi Makhachkala|Anzhi Makhachkala]] | caps14 = 29 | goals14 = 5 | years15 = 2016 | clubs15 = [[FC Volgar Astrakhan|Volgar Astrakhan]] | caps15 = 13 | goals15 = 5 | years16 = 2016 | clubs16 = [[FC Tobol|Tobol]] | caps16 = 18 | goals16 = 2 | years17 = 2017 | clubs17 = [[FC Anzhi Makhachkala|Anzhi Makhachkala]] | caps17 = 6 | goals17 = 0 | pcupdate = 14 May 2017 | ntupdate = }}
'''Shamil Saidbegovich Asildarov''' ({{lang-ru|Шамиль Саидбегович Асильдаров}}; born 18 May 1983) is a [[Russia]]n footballer of Avar ethnicity.
==Club career== Makhachkala-born Asildarov, is a journeyman striker who has played for eight different clubs in the last nine years.
On 2 July 2014, Asildarov signed a two-year contract with [[FC Anzhi Makhachkala|Anzhi Makhachkala]].<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:«Анжи» подписал контракты с семью игроками|url=http://www.fc-anji.ru/news/ru/club_news/anji_podpisal_kontrakti_s_sem_ju_igrokami020714/|publisher=[[FC Anzhi Makhachkala]]|accessdate=2 July 2014|language=Russian}}</ref> Leaving Anzhi after one season in June 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Asildarov parts with Anji|url=http://fc-anji.ru/news/en/fc_anji_news/asildarov_parts_with_anji200615/|publisher=FC Anzhi Makhachkala|accessdate=21 June 2015|date=20 June 2015}}</ref>
In February 2016, Asildarov went on trial with [[Kazakhstan Premier League]] side [[FC Shakhter Karagandy]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ШАХТЕР ПРОСМАТРИВАЕТ ИНОСТРАННЫХ ФУТБОЛИСТОВ|url=http://shahter.kz/main.php?mod=news&lang=rus&newsid=3002|publisher=[[FC Shakhter Karagandy]]|accessdate=2 February 2016|language=Russian|date=1 February 2016}}</ref>
On 13 June 2016, Asildarov signed a six-month contract with [[FC Tobol]] of the Kazakhstan Premier League.<ref>{{cite web|title=Тобол подписал Шамиля Асильдарова|url=http://www.fc-tobol.kz/rus/news/4286/|website=fc-tobol.kz|publisher=FC Tobol|accessdate=13 June 2016|language=Russian|date=13 June 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619212411/http://www.fc-tobol.kz/rus/news/4286/|archivedate=19 June 2016|df=}}</ref>
On 16 February 2017, Asildarov returned to Anzhi for a third stint with the club.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Anzhi Makhachkala]]|url=http://www.fc-anji.ru/news/ru/club_news/asil_darov_vernulsja_v_anji160217/|script-title=ru:Асильдаров вернулся в "Анжи"|date=16 February 2017|language=Russian}}</ref>
==Controversies== Recently whilst on a training camp in Turkey with [[FC Anzhi Makhachkala]] where he was on-trial, Asildarov was involved in a training ground brawl with also on-trial [[Aleksei Sapogov]] in which Sapogov had his jaw broken & required surgery. Anzhi spokesman Alexander Udaltsov was quoted as saying "What happened is an internal matter for the team".
==Achievements== * [[Russian Premier League]] bronze: 2006 * [[Russian Second Division]] Zone South top scorer: 2003 (31 goals)
